          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Remediate secrets</h4>
            <p>Confirmed secrets are automatically rewritten to use environment variables. Your source code is updated, a <code>.env</code> file is written with the real values, and <code>.gitignore</code> is updated.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Fix code vulns</h4>
            <p>For each real vulnerability, Claude provides a specific 1-line fix with a reason explaining why the current code is exploitable.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Verify</h4>
            <p>Re-scans after remediation to confirm all secrets are gone. Shows a final clean bill of health (or what's left to fix manually).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

